yes its in one big file...

I have added a video, to show that it does work.

# required libraries (which appear to not be installed on the linux labs).
- gml
- glew
- glut

# compile:
-> make

# run:
-> ./final

# compile and run:
-> make && ./final

# keyboard inputs
## state
'ESC' -> close program
'Z' -> disable/enable camera mouse movement
'X' -> disable/enable camera keyboard movement

### camera
'W' -> moves camera Forward
'S' -> moves camera Backward
'A' -> moves camera left
'D' -> moves camera right
'Q' -> moves camera up
'E' -> moves camera down
'O' -> use orthographic projection
'P' -> use perspective projection
'R' -> print camera information

## object collection
'1' -> select object 1 ("dragon")
'2' -> select object 2 ("grid")
'3' -> select object 3 ("table")

'N' or 'PAGE UP'  -> scale +
'M' or 'PAGE DOWN'-> scale -

'<' -> change object index +
'>' -> change object index -

## object
'UP ARROW'   -> translate +z
'DOWN ARROW' -> translate -z
'UP ARROW'   -> rotate +y 90degrees
'DOWN ARROW' -> rotate -y 90degrees

'U' or 'HOME' -> rotate +x
'J'           -> rotate -x
'H' or 'END'  -> rotate +y
'L'           -> rotate -y
'INSERT'      -> rotate +z

'Y' -> scale +
'I' -> scale -
'L' -> disable/enable draw

'T' -> print object information
